        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 29 at 7:25PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 725 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles east of Clemson, or 4 miles southeast of Norris, moving west at
5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Clemson, Central, Pendleton, Liberty, Norris, Northlake, and Sandy
Springs.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
